Dear [Manager’s Name],

Thank you for your message and for outlining your concerns. I would like to provide clarification regarding my work schedule and the specific dates mentioned.

For the past several years, the schedule we have consistently followed has been 6:00 AM to 3:00 PM Philippine Time. This schedule has remained unchanged regardless of when Daylight Saving Time started or ended, and there was no announcement or communication regarding any schedule adjustment. Based on this, 6:00 AM–3:00 PM PH time is the schedule I have continued to follow.

To address the specific instances mentioned:

December 8 – I acknowledge that I clocked in 26 minutes late. However, I ensured that I still completed my full 9-hour work schedule by logging off at 3:26 PM. I have attached a screenshot for your reference.

December 18 – I took my break at 1:56 PM and returned at 2:29 PM. I may have appeared idle for a few minutes afterward as I was not feeling well that day. However, I did not complete a full one-hour lunch break. I have attached a screenshot for your reference.

Following our recent one-on-one discussion, instances of tardiness have occurred only twice, each for 3–4 minutes, which happened because I had already begun checking emails and work-related items but unintentionally forgot to clock in on time.

I fully understand the concerns raised and appreciate the feedback. I would also like to respectfully request consideration regarding the requirement to work onsite. Morning traffic conditions in the Philippines are extremely challenging, and my travel time from home to the office typically takes 2–3 hours, depending on traffic. This would significantly affect my ability to consistently meet the early start time.

I am committed to maintaining consistent availability during my assigned working hours and to improving communication moving forward. I value my role and appreciate your time and consideration of the context provided.

Please let me know if any further clarification is needed.



