As you are aware, if either you or Madel are on leave on a given day, you are required to provide cover for each other to ensure there is adequate team coverage. Madel advised that she informed you that she would be on leave on 20th December. However, you did not report for work that day. Can you please explain the reason you did not report for work on 20th December and failed to notify myself or another member of management.



Thank you for the opportunity to clarify the circumstances regarding 20 December.

On 12 December, Madel informed me that she had submitted a PTO request for that date. However, I did not receive any update or official confirmation that her leave had been approved. Without such confirmation, and as I was already scheduled for a rest day, I followed our regular schedule and took the day off. This also allowed me to attend a pre-arranged medical appointment.

At the time, my understanding was that coverage arrangements were managed, as no official notification indicated otherwise. I hope this provides clarity, and I am happy to provide any additional details if required.

Yours sincerely,
Johnard Hidalgo




